The paper focuses on tuning and comparing deep learning models for text data, specifically word-embedding models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of tuning hyperparameters and the need for visual analytics to support developers in this process, which aligns with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions comparing high-level statistics and internal model behaviors, which suggests that Information Retrieval (cs.IR) may be relevant. Finally, the paper discusses the use of visual analytics to support developers, which aligns with the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
